title: For Sale:  M1A1 Carbine Stock
postcontent: For sale is a used, M1A1 Carbine stock.  I got this in a trade awhile back not knowing too much about what it was/is, I just wanted the barrel and receiver that came with the stock (barrel and receiver were marked "Inland" which is where my granddad worked so I wanted that part).  I have no need for it.  Stock has markings on the back, left side of "AAX."  I understand that this is from the Augusta Arsenal which was responsible for rebuilding M1A1s after the war.  Has "SA" stamped on the underside of the grip.  Springfield Arsenal made replacement parts after the war and shipped them to other arsenals for installation.  Buttplate is marked "B257614 *4."  The "*" looks like a wagon wheel, no an asterisk...there is just no key for a wagon wheel oddly enough.  Handguard is marked either "IH" or "HI."  Not sure which is right.  I've looked around and it seems these stocks are pretty valuable.  I make no guarantee that this thing is 100% real, paratrooper, brought home from the war so don't send me hate mail.  It looks real to me but hey, I wasn't alive in the 1940s.  Asking $1000 OBO, just trying to get my money back.  Open to trades:  firearms, gold, silver, anything MP5 related, pretty much anything except kids.  Don't offer to trade me your kids.  I've got enough.

The Beretta 21A Bobcat is a small pocket-sized semi-automatic pistol designed by Beretta. Current models are manufactured in the Beretta U.S.A. facility in Accokeek, Maryland.
The Beretta 21A Bobcat is a simple blowback pistol with a double-action/single-action (DA/SA) trigger mechanism. It is fitted with a frame-mounted manual thumb safety. 
One defining feature of this pistol is the 'tip-up' barrel. The barrel pivots on a pin under the muzzle so that the chamber may be loaded with the slide in the closed position. This simplifies loading, unloading, and checking load status. Finish is matt black with small amount of wear on edges.

title: For Sale:  AR 10.5" Pistol /w Sig Tac Brace like a SBR. Premium Parts
postcontent:
Here is a custom built 10.5" AR Pistol. Now what makes this stand out is the Sig Tac brace that is completely legal and transforms a pistol into a beast of a shooter. BUT TO BE CLEAR THIS IS A PISTOL, IT IS NOT A RIFLE. IT IS COMPLETELY LEGAL TO OWN AND DOES NOT REQUIRE ANY DIFFERENT REGISTRATION THAN ANY OTHER PISTOL DOES.

All the parts used in this custom build are premium, mil-spec or better parts. Obviously this is 5.56/.223 caliber and it has about 90 rounds down range. I Have other AR's and always wanted to go the pistol route, and when the Sig Tac brace became available it made it all worth it. The only reason I am selling is I want an IWI Tavor so the new toy has to go. 

Spartan Enhanced Billet Lower (Billet already more expensive than forged lowers. Enhanced means it has threaded pins so nothing goes flying if removing individual items. Also the magwell is flared and enhanced to allow drop free mag removals and also easier insertion on changes)  $160
PSA LPK ($65
12" Free Float Handguard upper(increases accuracy, allows positioning of rails wherever you choose) 1-9 Twist Barrel, with the 10.5" barrel a 1-7 is no more desirable until you get to 14" and above. $600
KAK Flash Can muzzle tip. Reduces recoil by pushing gases forward, but it does create a heck of a blast. Hence the Flash Can name. $35
A.R.M.S. Polymer Flip up battle sites $90
Magpul MIAD Grip with inserts (OD Green) $35
Mil-Spec Carbine Buffer Tube (Painted OD Green) $45
Magpul AFG (OD Green) $30
Magpul A.S.A.P. rear sling adapter $25
Primary Arms Red Dot site (the only thing that is not a premium item) With Quick Release Mount $100
Sig Tac Brace $120
Chrome RRA BCG with enhanced ejector $170  or make offer for a standard BCG $100

Add all that up and we are around the $1475 range as it sits. Like brand new. Will sell for $1050 that saves you the money for the build, taxes and shipping. Or make offer and I remove the Chrome BCG.

Everything is as you see included EXCEPT - Weapon Light, Sling, and Mag.

I have at the time a Chrome premium BCG installed. This was almost $200 at the time. If the rifle sells for what I am asking the BCG will go with the rifle. But I will entertain lower offers for a standard mil-spec black nitride BCG. If you know about BCG's the chrome is easier to clean after firing, and retains natural lubricity, reducing the need for lube.

I have other AR's so, the chrome BCG can go in those. Willing to hear offers though.
